  "body": "### Environment:\r\nmacOS Monterey 12.1\r\nnodejs 16.13.0\r\nhardhat 2.8.4\r\n\r\n### Setup\r\nI generated a sample project using `npx hardhat` and chose `Create a sample project`, then I modified `hardhat.config.js`:\r\n```js\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.6\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      chainId: 5678\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\nI tried to print the chainId in `scripts/sample-script.js`:\r\n```js\r\nconsole.log(await hre.ethers.getDefaultProvider().getNetwork())\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Problems\r\nI ran `npx hardhat scripts/sample-script.js --network hardhat` and got this:\r\n```text\r\nDeploying a Greeter with greeting: Hello, Hardhat!\r\nGreeter deployed to: 0x5FbDB2315678afecb367f032d93F642f64180aa3\r\n{\r\n  name: 'homestead',\r\n  chainId: 1,\r\n  ensAddress: '0x00000000000C2E074eC69A0dFb2997BA6C7d2e1e',\r\n  _defaultProvider: [Function: func] { renetwork: [Function (anonymous)] }\r\n}\r\n\r\n```",
