    "body": "@Brunnhild [`ethers.getDefaultProvider`](https://docs.ethers.io/v5/single-page/#/v5/api/providers/-%23-providers-getDefaultProvider) returns a provider connected to the mainnet. You want to do this instead:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconsole.log(await ethers.provider.getNetwork())\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `ethers.provider` object is added by the `hardhat-ethers` plugin, and it's an ethers provider connected to whatever network hardhat is connected to.",
